		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27428131">This thread is for the discussion of the Best Main Character of 2013.<br />
<br />
<strong>Event Guidelines</strong>:<ul><li> All eligible characters in an anime (excluding OVAs and films) must have appeared in at least one episode aired in the year.<br />
<li> All eligible characters in an OVA or film must have appeared in at least one of the BD/DVDs released in the year.</ul></ol><strong>Practices to Follow</strong>:<br />
<ul><li> Posts of any length are encouraged. However, in the case of very long posts, make sure each point made is concise or concise enough; it should always be easy to follow. In the case of very short posts, make sure what little you've said offers potential for further discussion.<br />
<li> Instead of writing from scratch, you can also try responding to a stance taken by a previous person, or elaborate on any interesting comment you've seen in the discussion so far.<br />
<li> Please try not to form too many comparisons. This makes it difficult for you to properly explain the significance of each one. Furthermore, you are limiting the scope of your message only to those who are familiar with the titles you are referencing.<br />
<li> Although it is natural for a conversation to take on a life of its own, avoid dragging the discussion completely off-topic.<br />
<li> Always be sure to exercise common sense, common courtesy, and clarity of argument.</ul></ol></div><div style="margin-top: 8px;"><em>Modified by nil-, 01-24-14, 2:10 PM</em></div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/clubs.php?cid=40791">QD</a><!--center--></div></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
