		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27689891">Here's my entry for cutest girl of 2013. Pretty much the same thing as best character.<br />
<br />
A miracle happened this year in Kyoto: an angel, in all her majesty and divinity, descended upon our mortal realm and graced humanity with her presence. It is should come as no surprise that this very embodiment of cuteness - Koto, is my favorite girl of 2013. Energetic, naïve, curious and disobedient, Koto personifies the very essence of childishness. Her appearance, in addition to being unbearably adorable, matches her personality perfectly. Her large shiny red eyes, almost always opened to their fullest, mirrors her curiosity and enigma brilliantly. Her childlike innocence is highlighted by an adorable smile as well as her cute school uniform. Her long hair, tied up into a ponytail, reinforces her unrelenting energy which is even further strengthened by her long limbs and rebellious posture. The character designers, wise as they are, did not resort to gimmicks such as colored hair to make a shallow declaration of her cuteness. When her hair is untied, however, it captures her inner vulnerability that is often obfuscated.<br />
<br />
With that said, there is far more to Koto than just her shiny red eyes and everlasting smile. She displays an astounding awareness of her situation and surroundings, giving a sense of maturity that one might not expect. This never feels out of character as it emphasizes her enigma rather than eccentricity. My favorite among the dozens of Koto’s positive traits, however, is her perseverance. Despite the burden that she bears, the hardships that she goes through and the vulnerabilities of her not yet fully developed mind, she always puts up a brave front that encourages and inspires not only the people around her, but the audience watching her through the looking glass. Kugimiya Rie does an impeccable job as Koto; I can’t imagine another person doing a better job than her in this role. Not only does her charming and charismatic voice perfectly match Koto’s demeanor, the childlike rawness which emanates through her voice further captures Koto’s rebellious nature. With such a perfect combination of brilliant characterization, lovely and well thought-out character design as well as an exquisite voice acting job by Kugimiya Rie, It is only inevitable that Koto would be the one to capture my heart for 2013 and perhaps retain it for years to come.<br />
<br />
Otherwise Yasaburou is probably #2 cutest girl from 2013.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
